# Django tests (backend)

When running Django `manage.py test` in this repo, use **`core.settings_test`** so the suite uses SQLite (`backend/test_db.sqlite3`) instead of creating a PostgreSQL test DB (which fails if `DB_USER` lacks `CREATEDB`).

**Examples:**

```bash
cd backend && python manage.py test --settings=core.settings_test
```

```bash
cd backend && python manage.py test apps.clusters.tests.MemberClusterBrowseAPITests --settings=core.settings_test
```

Do **not** default to `core.settings` for local test runs unless the user explicitly uses Postgres test databases.

Configuration lives in [`backend/core/settings_test.py`](backend/core/settings_test.py).
